From aa0eff379a2c586f73bf0f5630bf4998bc50cdd2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Sep 2025 12:13:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:HOSTAPD: Remove
 r19-Fill-Supported-Op-Classes-IE-based-on-country.patch

The patch r19-Fill-Supported-Op-Classes-IE-based-on-country.patch was
added to QSDK to address an issue, where the opclass 117 was getting
displayed on the AP operating on channel 40 in 40 MHz bandwidth.
The global opclass 117 is absent in China operating class table as per
the IEEE80211 spec. Hence country based opclass table was used in the
patch.

But the opclass 117 being absent in China operating class table, seems
to be a gap in the IEEE80211 spec. Ideally an opclass value should be
present for 40 MHz channels.

Therefore, remove the changes added by
r19-Fill-Supported-Op-Classes-IE-based-on-country.patch from QSDK,
to address this spec gap and make the AP behave like before.

Tag: REGULATORY

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Basuthkar <hbasuthk@qti.qualcomm.com>
